     <widget class="QWidget" name="gettingStartedTab">
      <attribute name="title">
       <string>Getting Started</string>
      </attribute>
      <layout class="QVBoxLayout" name="gettingStartedLayout">
       <item>
        <widget class="QTextEdit" name="gettingStartedTextEdit">
         <property name="readOnly">
          <bool>true</bool>
         </property>
         <property name="html">
          <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;style&gt;
body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 10px; }
h1 { color: #2c3e50; border-bottom: 2px solid #3498db; padding-bottom: 5px; }
h2 { color: #34495e; margin-top: 20px; }
.tip { background-color: #e8f4fd; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db; margin: 10px 0; }
.example { background-color: #f0f8f0; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #27ae60; margin: 10px 0; }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Welcome to Schema App v2!&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Schema App v2 helps you create &lt;strong&gt;schemas&lt;/strong&gt; without needing to know SHACL technical details. Think of schemas as blueprints for organizing information - like forms for collecting user data, product catalogs, or event management systems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;What You Can Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;📋 Create schemas from reusable building blocks (bricks)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🔄 Define how users interact with your data (flows)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;📤 Export your work as SHACL files for other systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🎯 Use templates for common scenarios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Quick Start Guide&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;div class="example"&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Example: Creating a Person Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
1. Click "New Schema" and name it "Person Profile"&lt;br&gt;
2. Select "Person" as your root brick (this is the main concept)&lt;br&gt;
3. Add component bricks like "Email" and "Phone" (these are additional details)&lt;br&gt;
4. Choose "Sequential" flow (step-by-step form)&lt;br&gt;
5. Click "Save Schema"&lt;br&gt;
6. Export as SHACL to use in other systems
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="tip"&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;💡 Pro Tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Start with a template! Click "Tools → Templates" to see common schemas like Person Profile, Product Catalog, or Event Management.
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Key Concepts Made Simple&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schema&lt;/strong&gt;: Your data blueprint (like a form template)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brick&lt;/strong&gt;: Reusable building block (like "Name", "Email", "Address")&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Root Brick&lt;/strong&gt;: Main building block (the "Person" in Person Profile)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Component Brick&lt;/strong&gt;: Additional details (the "Email" in Person Profile)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flow&lt;/strong&gt;: How users fill out your form (step-by-step, conditional, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</string>
         </property>
